.TH "bnx2i_send_conn_destroy" 9 "bnx2i_send_conn_destroy" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bnx2i_send_conn_destroy \- initiates iscsi connection teardown process
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" bnx2i_send_conn_destroy
.BI "(struct bnx2i_hba *hba "  ","
.BI "struct bnx2i_endpoint *ep "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hba" 12
adapter structure pointer
.IP "ep" 12
endpoint (transport identifier) structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
this routine prepares and posts CONN_OFLD_REQ1/2 KWQE to initiate
iscsi connection context clean-up process
